<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> be in trouble with someone • have trouble with someone</xh5><p> <i>be in trouble with someone—</i>suffer unhappiness or have problems because of smb.: He has <u>been in trouble with</u> the police arising out of his activities with the British Israelites.</p><p> <i>have trouble with someone—</i>1. have problems with smb. because of this person’s behavior: The Post Office is <u>having much trouble with</u> people who underpay their letters. 2. <i>= be in trouble with someone:</i> This wasn’t the first time that my family have <u>had trouble with</u> the police.</p> </entry>
